lyrics:
[Verse 1]
In a small town, where love's found, they come around to see
The big Ferris wheel and cotton candy, sweet as can be
Children laughing, music playing, under the moonlit sky
This carnival magic, takes me back to the days gone by

[Chorus]
Carnival lights, shining so bright, painting the night sky
Whirl and twirl, the tilt-a-whirl, in this sweet summertime
